{
  "stem": "11611.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So towards the end of my stay there, after about five, six months, we quickly ginned up six cases, which we threw into court and at least I had some kind of record left when I departed there, but I was actually there for about seven or eight months.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I sure did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Did I replace him?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was almost impossible to replace him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was shunted off to another role in the Department of Justice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Meanwhile, I-- there was a fellow who worked in the solicitor's office with extremely good legal credentials--",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Justice Department, Solicitor's office, in a very high level office of the Department of Justice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was a fellow who had great academic credentials, had spent some time working for the, what I regard as, distinguished firm of Williams and Connolly and was in the solicitor's office.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was interested in the job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I talked to him a couple times and initially told him I saw no prospects for him because my designated deputy was gonna get the job.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's all there was to it, and I never thought differently, but towards the end of the time I reached the conclusion that maybe it wasn't gonna work that way if I could help it.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A fellow named Allan Ryan who became, ultimately, the next director, mainly because he looked good to me and I presented him, really, to Phil Heymann who probably was instrumental in making the decision and a fellow named Mark Richards who was also in the division.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's the way it was resolved.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in many ways, it was not a gratifying experience.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never left.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
